x4freetext: THE ABSOLUTE CROSS SECTION OF U AT 90 DEGREES
WAS DETERMINED USING PROCEDURE DESCRIBED EARLIER.
OTHER ABSOLUTE CROSS SECTIONS WERE OBTAINED
BY COMPAIRING THE OBSERVED RELATIVE INTENSITIES
OF SCATTERED G-QUANTA WITH THE URANIUN VALUE

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Physical Review, Part C, Nuclear Physics, Vol.9, p.1153 (1974)

x4freetext: A BEAM OF 11.4 MEV PHOTONS, EXTRACTED FROM THE
CP-2 REACTOR, HAS BEEN USED IN A HIGH RESOLUTION
MEASUREMENTS OF THE DIFFERENTIAL CROSS SECTION FOR
PHOTON SCATTERING BY NUCLEI RANGING FROM PR-141
TO U-238. INELASTIC SCATTERING WHICH LEAVES THE
RESIDUAL NUCLEUS IN A STATE OF THE GROUND STATE
ROTATIONAL BAND, I.E. NUCLEAR RAMAN SCATTERING,
WAS MEASURED RELATIVE TO ELASTIC SCATTERING.
